manned  chemical rocket could be implemented <br>
now as  follows.<br>
1. You send an automated earth return vehicle,<br>
  to land on mars at the mars landing site   before<br>
  you launch the  1 way crewed  Mars ship from low <br>
earth orbit  to land at the landing site on Mars.<br>
2. You also send a nuclear electric generater with<br>
a Water  (H2O)  Electrolysis unit to the landing site with<br>
a 1 way soft landing on mars with one more launch,<br>
of another automated vehicle <br>
.<br>
3.  This will include  also  units for compressing, and <br>
liquifying Loh,  And the  Lox, and Loh  fuel storage<br>
 tanks for them.<br>
4.  After the manned  Mars landing water ice will collected<br>
on mars, melted ,then subjected to Electrolysis to<br>
 break the  H20 into H2 ,and O2 . Then it will be liquified<br>
and used to fuel the return vehicle to take the crew <br>
 to the earth .<br>
4. Both the manned mars  earth return ship , and <br>
the man to mars launch ship will burn H2 + O2,<br>
and have a specfic impulse of 450 seconds.<br>
They will both have a 5/1 mass ratio<br>
5. A 1 way decelerated mission to mars orbit from earth<br>
orbit  requires  just 6 kilometers a second in velocity to accomplish.A liitle more then this allows you to land<br>
 on mars.<br>
6. Six kilometers a second is  required for a 1 way <br>
decelerated flight from Mars orbit  to Earth <br>
Earth orbit. 7-8 kilometers a second is enough<br>
to lift off of the surface of Mars, accelecerate<br>
to Mars escape velocity, and then fly direct to earth <br>
orbit. Mars Gravity is just 38% of earth normal.*<br>
7. This means that an LOh + LoX burning rocket<br>
with a specific impulse of 450 seconds, and a mass<br>
ratio of 5/1 can make a 1 way declerated mission to<br>
the surface of  mars  from earth orbit , or a 1 way <br>
declerated mission from the  surface of Mars  to <br>
Earth orbit.<br>
8. If we use a 1000,000 kilogram H2 + O2  rocket for this<br>
 the numbers are as follows.<br>
9. There is 800,000 kilograms of fuel stored in <br>
two tanks with a mass of 160,000 kilograms.<br>
10.This leaves 40,000 kilograms of mass for the crewed<br>
ship, and its engines.  One space shuttle main <br>
engines can drive this reusable rocket from leo,<br>
or lift it off of mars because its gravity is just 38%<br>
of earth normal<br>
11. The Mars return ship has the same design <br>
as this craft, with a 5/1   mass ratio and one<br>
loh + lox stage with si = 450 seconds  . It will be<br>
 launched to Mars from leo.  Three km/sec blasts it out<br>
 of leo. Three km/sec decelerates it into Mars orbit.<br>
12. It then de-orbits itself by firing its engine  and soft <br>
lands at the mars landing site upright with its parachutes,<br>
and lands on its 4 legs while firing its engine right before touch down on mars.<br>
13. Then it uses The H2 + O2 Electrolysis  unit, and <br>
loh +lox liquidification unit to  refuel itself on Mars<br>
at the landing site .<br>
14. Later after refueling it takes off from mars<br>
with its crew, and it  flys direct to earth orbit. <br>
15. It needs about  5km/sec to achieve Mars Escape<br>
 velocity.<br>
16. With a 5/1 mass ratio it has 7.4 km/sec availible<br>
in total delta v.<br>
17. It burns up the rest of its Lox + loh fuel to <br>
decelerate into Earth orbit .Then it uses its steering<br>
 vernier thrusters to achieve a low earth orbit.<br>
18. Then the crew is picked up in leo  by a space shuttle<br>
or by a couple of Soyuz capsules ,and returns to earth. <br>
19. The Mars observer robot orbiter verified that there is<br>
 a lot of water ice on Mars in the year 2000..<br>
20. Zubrin proposed to use Lox + Methane for fuel,<br>
but the water ice on mars makes this obselete<br>
21.The zubrin approach can also be used to fly<br>
diect to all the nine planets, and back to leo<br>
starting from earth orbit, because you send the <br>
automated, and nuclear electric powered  loh + <br>
lox refueling system to every planet before a manned<br>
launch to get there occurrs.In this way you build<br>
a chain of interplanetary gas stations through the <br>
solar system. Then it becomes like driving your car.<br>
You can go anywhere on land on earth with your car<br>
if there is a gas station at the other end of the trip,<br>
to fill your gas tank. This allows this to be done in<br>
the solar system as well.<br>
